{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish a 'Less Scroll, More Soul' Bank Holiday: An Offline 'In-Community' Day",
        "additional_details": "We are an addicted, distracted nation. There are studies suggesting 67.4 million hours a day are lost to scroll and that children spend less time outdoors (<1hr) than inmates. We think loneliness, anxiety and polarisation are spiralling & all this before consideration of specific harms: exploitation, misinformation & more.\r\n \r\nWe have fewer bank holidays than almost anywhere in Europe.\r\n \r\nOne offline day a year could provide not only a critical reset but an opportunity for charities to showcase community volunteering opportunities.",
        "background": "We think the country urgently needs a breather: an annual reset for our overwhelmed, disconnected lives. A day to log off, look up & reconnect. A government-backed opportunity to build awareness of the grip tech has on us & remind us of what matters in a healthy society: people, place and presence.",
        "closed_at": null,
